gcloud CLI: 

    - gcloud auth login # Authenticate with Google Cloud
    - gcloud storage ls # List all the buckets within a project
    - gcloud compute configure-ssh # 
    - gcloud compute instances start <instance_name> --zone= uscentral-1
    - gcloud compute instances describe 
    - gcloud compute instances list
    - gcloud compute instances stop
    - bq ls # list all the datasets within a project
    - bq ls <datasetname> # List all the tables within a specified dataset. 
    - bq ls --max_results=<1000> <datasetname> # Specify the max number of records will be retrieved.

    - gsutil -m cp -r taxi_data_pq/ gs://bucket-spark-2026/taxi_data_pq # Copy a local file to a remote location in a bucket in gcs. 

Spark gcs connector: 

    - gs://hadoop-lib/gcs/gcs-connector-hadoop3-2.2.5.jar # Spark gsc connector

    reference: 
    https://docs.cloud.google.com/dataproc/docs/concepts/connectors/cloud-storage?hl=es-419

    Download it from gcs remote location to our machine: 
    - gsutil cp gs://hadoop-lib/gcs/gcs-connector-hadoop3-2.2.5.jar gcs-connector-hadoop3-2.2.5.jar
    